Bring a #pot of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} and pre-heat your #oven to 220 degrees.

Cut the @Echalion shallot{1}(peeled and chopped into small 1cm pieces) in half through the root, peel and chop into small 1cm pieces. Remove the core from the @yellow pepper{2}(core removed and chopped into roughly 2cm chunks) and chop into roughly 2cm chunks. Cut the @button mushrooms{1}(cut into roughly 1cm slices) into roughly 1cm slices and thinly slice the @mozzarella{2}(thinly sliced).

Add the @rigatoni pasta{300%g} to the boiling water and cook for ~{11%mins} until al dente (you will only need three-fifths of the bag of rigatoni). When the rigatoni is cooked, drain and drizzle over @olive oil{1%tbsp} to stop it all sticking together.

> 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle - taste it as you go to get it just right.

While your rigatoni is cooking, add @olive oil{1%tbsp} to a large #frying pan{} on medium high heat and throw in the @diced chorizo{1} and @British smoked bacon lardons{1}. Cook for about ~{4%mins} or until crisp, then remove with a #slotted spoon.

> You want to leave the oil in the pan to cook the veggies.

When your chorizo and pancetta has been removed, add @olive oil{1%tbsp} to the pan (no need to wash!), turn the heat to medium and add your shallot. Cook for ~{4%mins} before adding your chopped pepper and mushrooms. Turn the heat up slightly and sprinkle in @salt{1/2%tsp} and a good grind of @black pepper{}, mix together and cook for a further ~{7%mins} before adding the @chopped tomatoes{2}. Refill your tins a fifth with water, swill around and add this into the pan as well. Gently simmer the sauce for ~{5%mins}.

> This way, you don't have any wasted tomato!

Stir the @baby spinach{1}(stirred in) into your sauce (it will wilt as you stir!), then take the pan off the heat. Add your rigatoni, chorizo and pancetta into the pan and mix it all together.

Add a third of your rigatoni mixture into an #oven dish{} then layer over half your sliced mozzarella. Add another third of your rigatoni on top and layer over the rest of your mozzarella. Finally, spoon on the rest of your rigatoni, sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{4%tbsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and a really good grind of @black pepper{}. Pop in your oven to cook for ~{10%mins} or until the top is slightly browned and bubbly.

Serve in #bowls{} and devour!